import os

# 1. Load your data
# Replace 'your_data.csv' with the actual file path

# 2. Define the column names using their full names in the specified order (ALL 28)
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size", 
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point", 
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# 3. Select only numeric columns for correlation and plotting
numeric_df = df.select_dtypes(include=np.number)

# 4. Calculate the correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = numeric_df.corr()

# 5. Plot the Heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 16))  # Adjusted figure size

plt.title("Pearson Correlation Matrix Heatmap")

import pandas as pd

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from tensorflow import keras
from tensorflow.keras import layers
from tensorflow.keras.regularizers import l2
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers.schedules import ExponentialDecay
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

# Load and Prepare Data
df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')
# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]


# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Separate features and target
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Remove '%' and convert to float for ALL columns if necessary
for col in df.columns:
    if df[col].dtype == 'object' and any('%' in str(val) for val in df[col]):
        df[col] = df[col].astype(str).str.replace('%', '').astype(float) / 100

# Now re-separate features and target AFTER cleaning
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Scale features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# ... (Your build_optimized_ann function) ...
def build_optimized_ann(input_shape):
    # Learning rate schedule with slower decay
    lr_schedule = ExponentialDecay(
        initial_learning_rate=0.001, decay_steps=500, decay_rate=0.95
    )

    model = keras.Sequential([
        layers.Input(shape=(input_shape,)),
        layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.0005)),
        layers.Dropout(0.1),
        layers.Dense(64, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.0005)),
        layers.Dropout(0.1),
        layers.Dense(32, activation='relu', kernel_regularizer=l2(0.0005)),
        layers.Dense(16, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dense(1)  # Output layer for regression
    ])

    model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr_schedule),
                  loss='mse', metrics=['mae'])
    return model

# Implement K-Fold Cross-Validation
kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
results = {}

for fold_num, (train_index, val_index) in enumerate(kf.split(X_scaled), 1):
    X_train, X_val = X_scaled[train_index], X_scaled[val_index]
    y_train, y_val = y.iloc[train_index], y.iloc[val_index]

    # Build and train the model
    model = build_optimized_ann(input_shape=X_train.shape[1])

    early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=10, restore_best_weights=True)

    history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100, batch_size=8,
                        validation_data=(X_val, y_val),
                        callbacks=[early_stopping], verbose=0)

    # Evaluate the model
    y_pred = model.predict(X_val).flatten()
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_val, y_pred)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_val, y_pred)
    r2 = r2_score(y_val, y_pred)

    # Store results
    results[fold_num] = {'mse': mse, 'mae': mae, 'r2': r2, 'history': history.history, 'y_val': y_val, 'y_pred': y_pred}
    print(f"Fold {fold_num}: MSE={mse:.4f}, MAE={mae:.4f}, R2={r2:.4f}")

# Calculate Average Performance Metrics
avg_mse = np.mean([results[fold]['mse'] for fold in results])
avg_mae = np.mean([results[fold]['mae'] for fold in results])
avg_r2 = np.mean([results[fold]['r2'] for fold in results])

print("\nAverage Performance Metrics:")
print(f"  Average MSE: {avg_mse:.4f}")
print(f"  Average MAE: {avg_mae:.4f}")
print(f"  Average R2: {avg_r2:.4f}")

# Plot Training History
for fold in results:
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(results[fold]['history']['loss'], label='Training Loss')
    plt.plot(results[fold]['history']['val_loss'], label='Validation Loss')
    plt.title(f'Fold {fold} - Loss')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('Loss (MSE)')
    plt.legend()

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(results[fold]['history']['mae'], label='Training MAE')
    plt.plot(results[fold]['history']['val_mae'], label='Validation MAE')
    plt.title(f'Fold {fold} - MAE')
    plt.xlabel('Epoch')
    plt.ylabel('MAE')
    plt.legend()

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Display Test Results for Each Fold
for fold_num, result in results.items():
    print(f"\nTest Results for Fold {fold_num}:")
    
    # Create a DataFrame for better visualization
    result_df = pd.DataFrame({'Actual': result['y_val'], 'Predicted': result['y_pred']})
    print(result_df)

    # (Optional) Plot Actual vs. Predicted for each fold
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(result['y_val'], result['y_pred'])
    plt.plot([min(result['y_val']), max(result['y_val'])], [min(result['y_val']), max(result['y_val'])], '--', color='red') # Diagonal line for perfect prediction
    plt.xlabel("Actual Values")
    plt.ylabel("Predicted Values")
    plt.title(f"Fold {fold_num}: Actual vs. Predicted")
    plt.savefig("Desktop/Actual_vs_predicted3", format = 'png', dpi = 500)
    plt.show()

# Calculate overall test set performance metrics
all_y_true = np.concatenate([results[fold]['y_val'] for fold in results])
all_y_pred = np.concatenate([results[fold]['y_pred'] for fold in results])

overall_mse = mean_squared_error(all_y_true, all_y_pred)
overall_mae = mean_absolute_error(all_y_true, all_y_pred)
overall_r2 = r2_score(all_y_true, all_y_pred)

# Print overall test performance
print("\nOverall Test Performance Metrics:")
print(f"  MSE: {overall_mse:.4f}")
print(f"  MAE: {overall_mae:.4f}")
print(f"  R Score: {overall_r2:.4f}")

# --- Plot Results ---
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))

# 1. Actual vs. Predicted Scatter Plot
axes[0].scatter(all_y_true, all_y_pred, alpha=0.7)
axes[0].plot([min(all_y_true), max(all_y_true)], [min(all_y_true), max(all_y_true)], '--', color='red')
axes[0].set_xlabel("Actual Values")
axes[0].set_ylabel("Predicted Values")
axes[0].set_title("Actual vs. Predicted")

# 2. Residuals Plot
residuals = all_y_true - all_y_pred
axes[1].scatter(all_y_pred, residuals, alpha=0.6)
axes[1].axhline(y=0, color='red', linestyle='--')
axes[1].set_xlabel("Predicted Values")
axes[1].set_ylabel("Residuals (Errors)")
axes[1].set_title("Residuals Plot")

# 3. Distribution of Errors (Histogram)
axes[2].hist(residuals, bins=20, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
axes[2].set_xlabel("Residuals (Prediction Errors)")
axes[2].set_ylabel("Frequency")
axes[2].set_title("Error Distribution")

# Adjust layout and show
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("Desktop/Overall_Performance_Plots", format='png', dpi=500)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

# Load and Prepare Data
df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')
# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]


# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Remove '%' and convert to float for ALL columns if necessary
for col in df.columns:
    if df[col].dtype == 'object' and any('%' in str(val) for val in df[col]):
        df[col] = df[col].astype(str).str.replace('%', '').astype(float) / 100

# Separate features and target
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Scale features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Split Data into Training and Testing Sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Define the Random Forest Regressor with manually chosen best parameters
best_rf_model = RandomForestRegressor(
    n_estimators=200, 
    max_depth=20, 
    min_samples_split=5, 
    min_samples_leaf=2, 
    max_features='sqrt', 
    random_state=42
)

# Train the model
best_rf_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Make predictions on the test set
y_pred = best_rf_model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluate Performance
mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)

print("\nTest Set Performance:")
print(f"  MSE: {mse:.4f}")
print(f"  MAE: {mae:.4f}")
print(f"  R2: {r2:.4f}")

# Feature Importance
feature_importances = best_rf_model.feature_importances_
feature_names = X.columns
importance_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': feature_names, 'Importance': feature_importances})
importance_df = importance_df.sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)

print("\nFeature Importances:")
print(importance_df)

# Plot Feature Importance
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.barh(importance_df['Feature'], importance_df['Importance'], color='blue')
plt.xlabel("Feature Importance")
plt.title("Feature Importance from Random Forest Model")
plt.savefig("Desktop/RFR_Diagnostic)", format='png', dpi=500)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.subplots_adjust(left=0.3)
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.svm import SVR
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

# Load and Prepare Data
df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')
# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]



# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Remove '%' and convert to float for ALL columns if necessary
for col in df.columns:
    if df[col].dtype == 'object' and any('%' in str(val) for val in df[col]):
        df[col] = df[col].astype(str).str.replace('%', '').astype(float) / 100

# Separate features and target
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]


# 2. Preprocess the Data: Scale features using StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# 3. Split Data into Training and Testing Sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# 4. Define and Train the SVR Model
svr_model = SVR(kernel='poly', degree=3, C=40.0, epsilon=0.01)  # Example hyperparameters
svr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# 5. Make Predictions on the Test Set
y_pred = svr_model.predict(X_test)

# 6. Evaluate the Model
mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)

print("Test Set Performance:")
print(f"  MSE: {mse:.4f}")
print(f"  MAE: {mae:.4f}")
print(f"  R2: {r2:.4f}")

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

# --- Calculate Overall Test Set Performance ---
overall_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
overall_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
overall_r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)

# Print Overall Test Performance Metrics
print("\nOverall Test Performance Metrics:")
print(f"  MSE: {overall_mse:.4f}")
print(f"  MAE: {overall_mae:.4f}")
print(f"  R Score: {overall_r2:.4f}")

# --- Diagnostic Plots ---
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))

# 1. Actual vs. Predicted Scatter Plot
axes[0].scatter(y_test, y_pred, alpha=0.7, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
axes[0].plot([min(y_test), max(y_test)], [min(y_test), max(y_test)], '--', color='red')
axes[0].set_xlabel("Actual Values")
axes[0].set_ylabel("Predicted Values")
axes[0].set_title("Actual vs. Predicted")
axes[0].grid(True)

# 2. Residuals Plot
residuals = y_test - y_pred
axes[1].scatter(y_pred, residuals, alpha=0.6, color='purple', edgecolor='black')
axes[1].axhline(y=0, color='red', linestyle='--')
axes[1].set_xlabel("Predicted Values")
axes[1].set_ylabel("Residuals (Errors)")
axes[1].set_title("Residuals Plot")
axes[1].grid(True)

# 3. Distribution of Errors (Histogram)
axes[2].hist(residuals, bins=20, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7, color='green')
axes[2].set_xlabel("Residuals (Prediction Errors)")
axes[2].set_ylabel("Frequency")
axes[2].set_title("Error Distribution")
axes[2].grid(True)

# Adjust layout and save the figure
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("Desktop/SVM_Overall_Performance_Plots.png", format='png', dpi=500)
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.svm import SVR
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]

# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Remove '%' and convert to float for ALL columns if necessary
for col in df.columns:
    if df[col].dtype == 'object' and any('%' in str(val) for val in df[col]):
        df[col] = df[col].astype(str).str.replace('%', '').astype(float) / 100

# Separate features (X) and target (y)
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Scale features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# --- Train RFR Model ---
rfr_model = RandomForestRegressor(
    n_estimators=200, 
    max_depth=20, 
    min_samples_split=5, 
    min_samples_leaf=2, 
    max_features='sqrt', 
    random_state=42
)
rfr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Make predictions on the test set
y_pred_rfr = rfr_model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluate RFR performance
mse_rfr = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_rfr)
mae_rfr = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred_rfr)
r2_rfr = r2_score(y_test, y_pred_rfr)

print("RFR Test Set Performance:")
print(f"  MSE: {mse_rfr:.4f}")
print(f"  MAE: {mae_rfr:.4f}")
print(f"  R2: {r2_rfr:.4f}")

# --- Train SVM Model ---
svr_model = SVR(kernel='poly', degree=3, C=40.0, epsilon=0.01)
svr_model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Make predictions on the test set
y_pred_svm = svr_model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluate SVM performance
mse_svm = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_svm)
mae_svm = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred_svm)
r2_svm = r2_score(y_test, y_pred_svm)

print("SVM Test Set Performance:")
print(f"  MSE: {mse_svm:.4f}")

import pandas as pd

# Load and Prepare Data
df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')
# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]


# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Check data type of CTE column
print("CTE Column Data Type (Before Conversion):", df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].dtype)

# Convert CTE column to float (handle % if present)
df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].astype(str).str.rstrip('%')
df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"], errors='coerce') / 100

# Handle missing or incorrect values
if df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].isna().sum() > 0:
    print("Warning: Some values in CTE column could not be converted.")
    df = df.dropna(subset=["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"])  # Remove problematic rows

# Verify CTE range
print("CTE Min:", df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].min())
print("CTE Max:", df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].max())
# Separate features (X) and target (y)
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Scale features (only X, not y)
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Train the RFR Model (using best hyperparameters)
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
rfr_model = RandomForestRegressor(max_depth=20, max_features='sqrt', min_samples_leaf=2,
                                  min_samples_split=5, n_estimators=200, random_state=42)
rfr_model.fit(X_scaled, y)

# Define the objective function for Optuna
import optuna
def objective(trial):
    # Suggest values for TM and CY
    tm = trial.suggest_float('tm', 0, 5)  # Range for TM
    cy = trial.suggest_float('cy', 0, 6)  # Range for CY

    # Set other features to their mean values
    other_features_baseline = X.drop(["Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration"], axis=1).mean().values

    # Create input data for prediction
    sample = np.concatenate([np.array([tm, cy]), other_features_baseline]).reshape(1, -1)
    sample_scaled = scaler.transform(sample)

    # Predict CTE
    cte = rfr_model.predict(sample_scaled)[0]

    # Optuna minimizes the objective, so return negative CTE for maximization
    return -cte

# Create an Optuna study and optimize
study = optuna.create_study(direction='minimize')
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=1000)  # Adjust n_trials as needed

# Get the best and worst results
best_trial = study.best_trial
best_tm = best_trial.params['tm']
best_cy = best_trial.params['cy']
best_cte = -best_trial.value  # Convert back to positive CTE

# Find the worst trial
worst_trial = max(study.trials, key=lambda t: t.value)
worst_tm = worst_trial.params['tm']
worst_cy = worst_trial.params['cy']
worst_cte = -worst_trial.value  # Convert back to positive CTE

print(f"Best CTE: {best_cte:.4f} achieved with TM: {best_tm:.2f}, CY: {best_cy:.2f}")
print(f"Worst CTE: {worst_cte:.4f} achieved with TM: {worst_tm:.2f}, CY: {worst_cy:.2f}")

# --- Visualization ---
# Extract all trials for plotting
tm_values = [trial.params['tm'] for trial in study.trials]
cy_values = [trial.params['cy'] for trial in study.trials]
cte_values = [-trial.value for trial in study.trials]

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
scatter = plt.scatter(tm_values, cy_values, c=cte_values, cmap='viridis', s=20)
plt.colorbar(scatter, label="Cuttings Transport Efficiency (CTE)")
plt.scatter(best_tm, best_cy, color='red', marker='*', s=200, label="Best CTE")
plt.scatter(worst_tm, worst_cy, color='blue', marker='*', s=200, label="Worst CTE")
plt.xlabel("Terminalia Mantaly Concentration (TM)")
plt.ylabel("Cocoyam Concentration (CY)")
plt.title("Optimization of TM and CY for Cuttings Transport Efficiency (Optuna)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Desktop/tm_cy_optimization_optuna.png", format='png', dpi=300)
plt.show()

CTE Max: 0.7332

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import optuna
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Load and Prepare Data
df = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv', delimiter=',')

# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" (CTE) to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df = df[[col for col in df.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]

# Define column names
column_names = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df.columns = column_names

# Convert CTE column to float (handle % if present)
df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].astype(str).str.rstrip('%')
df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = pd.to_numeric(df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"], errors='coerce') / 100

# Handle missing values
df = df.dropna(subset=["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"])

# Separate features (X) and target (y)
X = df.drop("Cuttings Transport Efficiency", axis=1)
y = df["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# Scale features (only X, not y)
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Train the RFR Model
rfr_model = RandomForestRegressor(
    max_depth=20, max_features='sqrt', min_samples_leaf=2,
    min_samples_split=5, n_estimators=200, random_state=42
)
rfr_model.fit(X_scaled, y)

# Define the Optuna Objective Function
def objective(trial):
    # Suggest values for TM and CY
    tm = trial.suggest_float('tm', 0, 3)  # Range for TM
    cy = trial.suggest_float('cy', 0, 3)  # Range for CY

    # Set other features to their mean values
    other_features_baseline = X.drop(["Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration"], axis=1).mean().values

    # Create input data for prediction
    sample_dict = {
        "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration": [tm],
        "Cocoyam Concentration": [cy]
    }
    
    # Add the other features with their mean values
    for feature, value in zip(X.drop(["Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration"], axis=1).columns, other_features_baseline):
        sample_dict[feature] = [value]
    
    # Convert to DataFrame with correct column order
    sample_df = pd.DataFrame(sample_dict, columns=X.columns)
    
    # Scale the input
    sample_scaled = scaler.transform(sample_df)
    
    # Predict CTE
    cte = rfr_model.predict(sample_scaled)[0]

    # **Allow Extrapolation but Clip to 1**
    cte = min(cte, 1.0)

    # Optuna minimizes the objective, so return negative CTE for maximization
    return -cte

# Optimize with Optuna
study = optuna.create_study(direction='minimize')
study.optimize(objective, n_trials=1500)

# Best and Worst Trials
best_trial = study.best_trial
best_tm = best_trial.params['tm']
best_cy = best_trial.params['cy']
best_cte = -best_trial.value  # Convert back to positive CTE

worst_trial = max(study.trials, key=lambda t: t.value)
worst_tm = worst_trial.params['tm']
worst_cy = worst_trial.params['cy']
worst_cte = -worst_trial.value  # Convert back to positive CTE

print(f"Best CTE: {best_cte:.4f} achieved with TM: {best_tm:.2f}, CY: {best_cy:.2f}")
print(f"Worst CTE: {worst_cte:.4f} achieved with TM: {worst_tm:.2f}, CY: {worst_cy:.2f}")

# --- Visualization ---
tm_values = [trial.params['tm'] for trial in study.trials]
cy_values = [trial.params['cy'] for trial in study.trials]
cte_values = [-trial.value for trial in study.trials]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
scatter = plt.scatter(tm_values, cy_values, c=cte_values, cmap='viridis', s=20)
plt.colorbar(scatter, label="Cuttings Transport Efficiency (CTE)")
plt.scatter(best_tm, best_cy, color='red', marker='*', s=200, label="Best CTE")
plt.scatter(worst_tm, worst_cy, color='blue', marker='*', s=200, label="Worst CTE")
plt.xlabel("Terminalia Mantaly Concentration (TM)")
plt.ylabel("Cocoyam Concentration (CY)")
plt.title("Optimization of TM and CY for Cuttings Transport Efficiency (Optuna)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Desktop/tm_cy_optimization_optuna.png", format='png', dpi=300)
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.neighbors import NearestNeighbors
from scipy.stats import ttest_rel, wilcoxon
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# --- Load and Prepare Data ---

# Load TM/CY dataset
df_tmcy = pd.read_csv('Documents/Goodydataset.csv')  # Adjust file path if needed

# Move "Cuttings Transport Efficiency" (CTE) to the last column SAFELY
col_to_move = "CTR"
df_tmcy = df_tmcy[[col for col in df_tmcy.columns if col != col_to_move] + [col_to_move]]

# Define column names for TM/CY dataset
column_names_tmcy = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df_tmcy.columns = column_names_tmcy

# Convert CTE column to float (handle % if present)
df_tmcy["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = df_tmcy["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"].astype(str).str.rstrip('%')
df_tmcy["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"] = pd.to_numeric(df_tmcy["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"], errors='coerce') / 100

# Handle missing values
df_tmcy = df_tmcy.dropna(subset=["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"])

# Load PAC-R dataset
df_pacr = pd.read_csv('Downloads/PACR.csv')  # Adjust file path if needed

# Define column names for PAC-R dataset
column_names_pacr = [
    "Cuttings Concentration", "Rate of Penetration", "Mud Flowrate", "Cutting Size",
    "Effective Mud Viscosity", "Effective Mud Weight", "Annular Velocity", "Mud Lifting Capacity",
    "Mud Cutting Rise Velocity", "Drag Coefficient", "Plastic Viscosity", "Yield Point",
    "PAC-R", "Dummy", "Cuttings Transport Efficiency"
]
df_pacr.columns = column_names_pacr

# --- Separate features (X) and target (y) ---

# TM/CY dataset: Drop TM, CY, and CTE
X_tmcy = df_tmcy.drop(["Cuttings Transport Efficiency", "Terminalia Mantaly Concentration", "Cocoyam Concentration"], axis=1)
y_tmcy = df_tmcy["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# PAC-R dataset: Drop PAC-R, dummy column, and CTE
X_pacr = df_pacr.drop(["Cuttings Transport Efficiency", "PAC-R", "Dummy"], axis=1)
y_pacr = df_pacr["Cuttings Transport Efficiency"]

# --- Scale features separately using StandardScaler ---
scaler_tmcy = StandardScaler()
X_tmcy_scaled = scaler_tmcy.fit_transform(X_tmcy)

scaler_pacr = StandardScaler()
X_pacr_scaled = scaler_pacr.fit_transform(X_pacr)

# --- Find Nearest Neighbors ---
nbrs = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=1, algorithm='ball_tree').fit(X_tmcy_scaled)
distances, indices = nbrs.kneighbors(X_pacr_scaled)

# --- Matched CTE values ---
matched_cte_tmcy = y_tmcy.iloc[indices.flatten()].values

# --- Statistical Comparison ---

# 1. Paired t-test
t_statistic, p_value_ttest = ttest_rel(y_pacr, matched_cte_tmcy)

# 2. Wilcoxon signed-rank test (handle zero-difference issue)
try:
    statistic_wilcoxon, p_value_wilcoxon = wilcoxon(y_pacr, matched_cte_tmcy)
    print(f"Wilcoxon signed-rank test: statistic = {statistic_wilcoxon:.4f}, p-value = {p_value_wilcoxon:.4f}")
except ValueError:
    print("Wilcoxon test not performed due to zero-difference issue.")

print(f"Paired t-test: t-statistic = {t_statistic:.4f}, p-value = {p_value_ttest:.4f}")

# 3. Average Difference
avg_diff = np.mean(y_pacr - matched_cte_tmcy)
print(f"Average Difference in CTE (PAC-R - TM/CY): {avg_diff:.4f}")

# 4. Scatter Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.scatter(y_pacr, matched_cte_tmcy, alpha=0.5)
plt.plot([min(y_pacr), max(y_pacr)], [min(y_pacr), max(y_pacr)], 'k--', lw=2)  # Diagonal line
plt.xlabel("CTE (PAC-R Dataset)")
plt.ylabel("CTE (TM/CY Dataset - Matched)")
plt.title("Comparison of CTE for Matched Data Points")
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Desktop/Hello", format='png', dpi=700)
plt.show()

# 5. Compare Best TM/CY CTE to PAC-R Distribution
best_tmcy_cte = 0.6104  # From your Optuna optimization
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.hist(y_pacr, bins=20, alpha=0.7, label="PAC-R CTE Distribution", color="blue")
plt.axvline(x=best_tmcy_cte, color='r', linestyle='--', label="Best TM/CY CTE")
plt.xlabel("Cuttings Transport Efficiency (CTE)")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.title("Comparison of Best TM/CY CTE to PAC-R CTE Distribution")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig("Desktop/Hi", format="png", dpi=700)
plt.show()
